{"body": "That test should still be there to make sure that regression keeps working moving forward; it is definitely re-introduced now.\r\n\r\nIf the new record is being created off of an association, it should have reference to the owning object of the association and then that test should pass.  If the creation attributes don't exist, the new object has no reference to the owner.\r\n\r\nShouldn't that test have been left and a solution that worked with the regression be implemented instead?  Kind of defeats the purpose of the test in the first place.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3240728", "created_at": "2011-12-21T22:36:06Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/4122#issuecomment-3240728", "updated_at": "2011-12-21T22:36:06Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 4122, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/akaspick/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/akaspick/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/akaspick/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/akaspick", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/akaspick/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/akaspick", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/akaspick/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/898bf26eb61308fe717a243441cc615d?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F82c3cf12914d43d34d8883ec88307da2.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/akaspick/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/akaspick/received_events", "gravatar_id": "898bf26eb61308fe717a243441cc615d", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/akaspick/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "akaspick", "type": "User", "id": 24056, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/akaspick/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52382c44bd3543c15100f1c6"}, "id": 3240728, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/4122"}
